##Those who are not suffering from NCP are suffering in silence..

Micro Signal Xinminzhoukan

Function description, depth and angle —— this is what we can do.

As a doctor, I know very well that behind every new pneumonia patient, there is a suffering family, the difficulty can be overcome, we need to bear together. And as the city of Wuhan closed longer and longer, some non-new coronary pneumonia patients, the same suffering in silence.

Dictation | Zheng Hua
Tidying | Wu Xue
At eight o'clock in the morning, when I got off the night shift and my shift colleague arrived on the dot, I ordered the patient in charge of the ward to go into the hospital dressing room, take off the protective clothing, take off the goggles, and breathe heavily. For a long time did not pay attention to the scenery outside the hospital window, as if the trees issued a new bud. As a doctor in the Department of anesthesiology of Huazhong University of Science and Technology Affiliated Tongji Hospital, February 29 was the ninth day of my return to work, has Been my routine for almost a week.
Photo provided by interviewees wearing protective clothing in the ward of Huazhong University of Science and Technology

I think back to this month, my heart of suffering, hope, tangled, all mixed together, not a moment to stop. I usually work very busy, the Spring Festival holiday, was going to spend a good time with his family. But on January 24, the outbreak, I decided to give up leave to return to work, the family is also very supportive. You ask me why I didn't return to work until mid-february, because on January 28th, when I wasn't on duty, something unexpected happened.
That day, my wife suddenly had a fever. Her temperature was less than 38 °C, not high fever. At the time, it wasn't clear whether it was NCP, but given the uncertainty of the virus and my professional sensitivity as a doctor, I made a decision: it had to be isolated, no matter what. My mother-in-law and I set aside our hands to tidy up the master bedroom with the bathroom, and on the first day we put our loved ones in isolation and locked it. I have two children, a 7 year old, a 3 year old, at first they do not understand, crying and insisted to open the door handle to find his mother. Later, the video a few times, the child had no way, also can be left in peace.
After the separation of our loved ones, we began to treat the symptoms and take antipyretics to lower the temperature. Before the Three Meals a Day, I would call for dinner via wechat or a video link. I would put the food in the lunch box and leave it at the door. It was almost like being in prison. The next day, the temperature suddenly jumped to a high fever of 39 °C, and always repeated, afternoon and evening in particular obvious. Fortunately, the lover disposition is bright, everything thinks happily, the state of mind is also quite good.
February 18, Huazhong University of Science and Technology Affiliated Tongji Hospital in the Sino French new city district nurses are handing over the Bantu | Xinhua news agency

February 3, repeated high fever to the seventh day, my lover has not been improved, I worried. Decided to take her to the clinic for a C.T. Sure enough, the C.T. showed double lung infection and a high degree of suspected new coronary pneumonia. Hospital beds were in short supply and my colleagues were tired and I didn't want to bother them, even though I was at the hospital where I worked. I took my lover home that day. On 4 February, the hospital informed one of its branches that it had changed to a designated hospital and that loved ones could be admitted.
I packed up the necessaries of life, drove my lover to go, the team was the Shandong medical team, take care of very thoughtful. Although I wore a mask and took precautions along the way, I decided not to return to work for a while after I had settled my lover for safety's sake. After seven days of isolation at home, I called the Medical Office of Tongji Hospital to explain the circumstances of the contact, he's clean as a whistle. Put in for duty. About four or five times, and on February 20th, I officially returned to work.
Feb. 18, a patient is discharged from the new severe pneumonia ward in the Sino French Xincheng district of the Huazhong University of Science and Technology

After 14 days, the lover nucleic acid test is normal, the official discharge, needs the home isolation. I am not afraid to go to work, the most worry is the mother-in-law at home alone, with two children, too noisy, but also take care of love and just had lung cancer surgery father-in-law. If you don't pay attention, you could cross-infect. A few days before work, I began training my mother-in-law every day on how to protect and disinfect. For example, mix 84 disinfectant solution into a certain concentration, wipe the door handle, toilet, toilet seat and other public contact place; after using chopsticks, with ultraviolet light and high-temperature ozone disinfection cabinet. Up until now, we've been fine, which means it's working.
For example, the waste from the toilet paper basket must be sprayed with disinfectant before being thrown downstairs, because if it carries the virus, it will endanger the health of the sanitation workers. Before lover is in hospital, next door on the bed is a pick up garbage to live old woman, because garbage carries virus and be infected, so must deal with, do not harm people.
Zheng Hua's mother wrote him a note before he went to the front line
On the 20th I went to work and was assigned to the new pneumonia intensive care unit, which had more than forty patients and 18 doctors, including the infectious and respiratory departments. Unlike the initial "fatigue challenge, " we have five groups of people working in shifts, one group during the day, one group at night, can basically guarantee two days, three days off. The hospital also stressed that as long as you feel uncomfortable, do not insist, must be the first time to report.

There are a lot fewer patients admitted to critical care hospitals, and on average one or two cases are cured every day. However, I personally feel that the current figures do not allow us to relax our vigilance, especially among discharged patients and those who are likely to be in close contact with patients, close observation is also needed to reduce the risk of infection. Working nine days, I received a lot of patients'families, because I can not meet with relatives, can only send word to me. But the most obvious is the psychological contrast between the family and the patient. Family members express concern, but patients often do not report the bad news, he will not say that the drug bad, not to say that their whole body is uncomfortable sleep can not sleep, usually convey positive words, in fact, also to cheer themselves.
Dr Cheng Wah communicates with patients with new coronary pneumonia

Dr. Zheng Hua sees patients with new coronary pneumonia
Fang Fang, a writer in Wuhan, says that a grain of ash from the age, when it falls on a person's head, is a mountain. The only thing we have to do is take it all on. As a doctor, I know very well that behind every new pneumonia patient, there is a suffering family, the difficulty can be overcome, we need to bear together. And as the city of Wuhan closed longer and longer, some non-new coronary pneumonia patients, the same suffering in silence.
On February 28, I got off the night shift and drove back to the isolation hotel, half an hour's drive from Tongji Hospital. Just after washing her face and sitting down, a page of "someone registered" popped up on the computer screen. The patient was a patient with advanced lung cancer. The couple were about 60 or 70 years old. The Old Lady said she knew she was dying and did not want to be in the midst of an epidemic, put a strain on the doctor. But every day, I couldn't sleep because of the pain, and I ran out of painkillers, and I couldn't get any, so I was begging for a prescription.
In the isolation hotel, I use a computer to treat non-new coronary pneumonia patients

I was so hurt by what she said. Prescribed her some pain medication and mailed it to the patient at the address. Later, I saw four or five patients with neck and shoulder pain. A week of House calls, the number of patients is not much, I think most do not know the hospital and "Cloud Clinic" service. On February 14, "Tongjiyun clinic" officially launched on the "handhelds Tongji" APP, click the button of online consultation, you can enter the choice of departments, 135 experts, 50 departments, 469 doctors open video and medical consultation, can be issued online prescription, achieve off-line distribution of drugs.
"Cloud Clinic" consultation page for patients with pictures and texts, respondents for pictures

Pharmacy after the delivery of drugs by express mail, postage to pay, parcel status can be traced | Huazhong University of Science and Technology Affiliated Tongji Hospital official website

Every department has at least one doctor on-line video consultation every morning and morning. I am a deputy senior professional title. I have been working here since I graduated from the Tongji Medical College in 2004. But in the cloud clinic, no matter is deputy high or high, registration fees are the same, only a few dollars can, registration success, doctors will be based on the same outpatient registration, in turn call.
Last night, at 11:30, I received another picture and text consultation from a patient with skin rash. Although it is a small problem, it has a great impact on the quality of life, which I particularly understand, i learned today that the hospital's Oncology Department has opened up some beds for non-ncp patients, but the admission process may be different than before, such as family members can not be accompanied, the need to live in isolation and so on. I can help you if you need me.
Picture shows Dr Cheng Wah wearing protective clothing in the ward of Huazhong University of Science and Technology

In my opinion, helping non-ncp patients to solve their problems will help them better cope with home isolation. After work, I learned that love home, fever and repeated, at first is a fever, take medicine and back. I knew this was not a good sign. She was still isolated in the master bedroom. Her mother in law, a woman in her sixties, was taking care of the family's food and shelter and the risk of infection. I could do nothing to help them, the only thing we can do is cheer each other up on video.
Doctors and patients alike may have their struggles, but on the bright side, at least the hard times are over. As a doctor, I believe that there will be a day when we can cure the patients we have treated, control the spread of new infections, and take good care of the non-new pneumonia patients.
